               <sense xml:id="Dmain" xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann"> <subc>I,1</subc> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ለበሰ፡</foreign> occurrit <ref cRef="Luc." loc="12,7">Luc. 12,7</ref> <lbl expand="romanae editionis">rom.</lbl>, modo ne errore typographi exscriptum sit) <gramGrp> <pos expand="Subjunctivus">Subj.</pos> </gramGrp> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይልበስ፡</foreign>, sed <ref cRef="Marc." loc="6,9">Marc. 6,9</ref> utraque editio <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይልብሱ፡</foreign> praebet [i.q. <foreign xml:lang="he">לָבַשׁ</foreign> et <foreign xml:lang="he">לָבֵשׁ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܠܒܶܫ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="ar">لَبِسَ</foreign>, amh. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለበሰ፡</foreign>] <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> induere </t:quote></cit> vestem, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><t:quote xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"> indutum esse </t:quote></cit> veste; <lbl expand="cum">c.</lbl> <gramGrp> <case value="accusativus">Acc.</case> </gramGrp> vestis, ut <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለብሰ፡ ባዕደ፡ አልባሰ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="1 Reg." loc="28,8">1 Reg. 28,8</ref>; <ref cRef="Gen." loc="37,23">Gen. 37,23</ref>; <ref cRef="Apoc." loc="1,13">Apoc. 1,13</ref>; <ref cRef="Jes." loc="37,1">Jes. 37,1</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሞጣሕተ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Gen." loc="38,14">Gen. 38,14</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὅπλα</foreign> <ref cRef="Rom." loc="13,12">Rom. 13,12</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልበሱ፡ ሐፂነ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Jer." loc="26,3">Jer. 26,3</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይለብሱ፡ ብሩሀ፡ ወንጹሐ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Apoc." loc="15,6">Apoc. 15,6</ref>. Saepissime transfertur ad alias res: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኀፍረተ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Job" loc="8,21">Job 8,21</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ስብሐተ፡</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="gez">ብርሃነ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Ps. " loc="103,2">Ps.  103,2</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ጽድቀ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Job" loc="29,14">Job 29,14</ref>; <ref cRef="Jes." loc="59,17">Jes. 59,17</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኀይለ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Job" loc="40,5">Job 40,5</ref>; <ref cRef="Jes." loc="51,9">Jes. 51,9</ref>; <ref cRef="Jes." loc="52,1">Jes. 52,1</ref>; <ref cRef="Luc." loc="24,49">Luc. 24,49</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ልበ፡ እኩየ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="4 Esr." loc="1,20">4 Esr. 1,20</ref>; <ref cRef="4 Esr." loc="1,25">4 Esr. 1,25</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዘኢይመውት፡</foreign> <ref cRef="4 Esr." loc="14,12">4 Esr. 14,12</ref>; <ref cRef="1 Cor." loc="15,49">1 Cor. 15,49</ref>; <ref cRef="Christum Rom." loc="13,14">Christum Rom. 13,14</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐዲሰ፡ ብእሴ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Eph." loc="4,24">Eph. 4,24</ref>; al. In libris theologicis crebrius occurrit: Christus vel <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὁ λόγος</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለብሰ፡ ነፍስትነ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Rom." loc="8,3">Rom. 8,3</ref> <lbl expand="romanae editionis">rom.</lbl>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሥጋ፡ እምድንግል፡</foreign> <ref cRef="Clem." loc="7">Clem. f. 7</ref>; <ref cRef="Clem." loc="13">Clem. f. 13</ref>; Cyr. </sense>
               
